OL,3,CDenis Law was 'cornerstone' of
OL,4,CManchester United success
OL,6,FSpeaking before the match, Sir Alex
OL,7,FFerguson hailed Law as the "greatest
OL,8,FScottish player of all time" and
OL,9,Fdescribed him as the "cornerstone" of
OL,10,FManchester United's success.
OL,12,FLaw, who won two league titles with
OL,13,FUnited and was a member of their
OL,14,FEuropean Cup-winning team under Sir
OL,15,FMatt Busby in 1968 when they became
OL,16,Fthe first English club to lift the
OL,17,Ftrophy, died on Friday aged 84.
OL,19,FLaw won the Ballon d'Or in 1964 - the
OL,20,Fonly Scottish player to do so - and
OL,21,Fclaimed 55 caps for his country.
